4)What is the Box Model in CSS?
The CSS Box Model describes how every HTML element is structured and how space is calculated around it.
Each element is a rectangular box made of the following four parts:

Content : The actual text or image inside the box.

Example: Text inside a <div> or an image inside a container.

Padding :  The space inside the box, between the content and the border.

Use: Increases space around the content but inside the element.

Border : The line or edge that goes around the padding and content.

Use: Visually separates elements or adds styling.

Margin : The space outside the border, between this element and other elements.

Use: Creates distance between boxes.
