5)give defination of all postion values?
1. static (default)
Definition: The element is positioned according to the normal document flow.

Note: top, left, right, bottom do not work.

Use case: When you don‚Äôt want to change the default layout.

2. relative
Definition: The element is positioned relative to its normal position.

Note: You can use top, left, right, bottom to shift it from where it would normally appear.

Use case: Often used as a reference for absolutely positioned child elements.

3. absolute
Definition: The element is positioned relative to the nearest positioned ancestor (relative, absolute, or fixed). If no such ancestor, it's relative to <html> (page).

Note: It is removed from normal flow, so it doesn't affect or get affected by nearby elements.
Moves with page scroll.
4. fixed üëç
Definition: The element is positioned relative to the browser window, and it stays in place even when you scroll the page.

Note: It is also removed from the document flow.
